The paper discusses a simulation model for exploring the relation between the number of submissions and the overall quality of academic journals under peer review. This involves distributed parallel systems, which suggests a focus on topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper deals with academic journals and peer review, which could fall under categories such as cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
